The R programming language is our language of choice for data analysis. Not only is it open-source and freely-available, but it is capable of generating publication-quality images and has a large user-base amongst the scientific community. It also promotes the practice of \textbf{Reproducible Research}.
However, it comes with a steep learning-curve especially for those without prior exposure to command-line. We are taking the following steps to help with the transition from GraphPad Prism.\vspace{1cm}

\begin{itemize}
\item{Promote the RStudio GUI for R}
\item{Support forum for C.I. staff}
\item{Availability of R classes at The Department of Genetics}
\item{Bespoke training on R graphics with online materials}
\item{Worked-examples of how to conduct typical GraphPad Prism analyses in R}
\item{Maintain a repository of useful R literature and resources}
\end{itemize}

    \end{block}
    
